text: Move him into the sun--&& Gently its touch awoke him once,
Gently its touch awoke him once,&& At home, whispering of fields unsown.
At home, whispering of fields unsown.&& Always it awoke him, even in France,
Always it awoke him, even in France,&& Until this morning and this snow.
Until this morning and this snow.&& If anything might rouse him now
If anything might rouse him now%% The kind old sun will know.
The kind old sun will know.&& Think how it wakes the seeds--
Think how it wakes the seeds--&& Woke, once, the clays of a cold star.
Woke, once, the clays of a cold star.&& Are limbs so dear-achieved, are sides
Are limbs so dear-achieved, are sides%% Full-nerved,--still warm,--too hard to stir?
Full-nerved,--still warm,--too hard to stir?&& Was it for this the clay grew tall?
Was it for this the clay grew tall?&& --O what made fatuous sunbeams toil
--O what made fatuous sunbeams toil%% To break earth's sleep at all?
